R1: The N stage for breast cancer is determined by the number of lymph nodes with metastasis.
R2: N0 indicates no lymph node metastasis.
R3: N1 indicates metastasis in 1-3 axillary lymph nodes.
R4: N2 indicates metastasis in 4-9 axillary lymph nodes.
R5: N3 indicates metastasis in 10 or more axillary lymph nodes.
R6: Avoid using report-specific information for rule creation.
R7: Ensure rules are general and applicable to the specific cancer type and the AJCC staging system.
